OL,3,CArsonist who killed pensioner in
OL,4,C'random' house fire guilty of murder
OL,6,FThe fire, which was started in a
OL,7,Fwheelie bin that Gorrell had moved to
OL,8,Fblock the front door of the property
OL,9,Fin Holyhead Road, engulfed the home
OL,10,Fand left Mr Edwards with severe
OL,11,Finjuries which he died from in
OL,12,Fhospital on May 25.
OL,14,FHis wife Doreen Edwards, who was 81 at
OL,15,Fthe time of the fire, and their two
OL,16,Fadult sons Carl, 60, and Mark Edwards,
OL,17,F57, who were both staying the night at
OL,18,Ftheir parents' home, were all injured
OL,19,Fand taken to hospital.
