OL,3,CArsonist who killed pensioner in
OL,4,C'random' house fire guilty of murder
OL,6,F"He didn't alert anyone to the fire.
OL,7,FIf he had been out to cause a bit of
OL,8,Fmischief or a bit of damage, he
OL,9,Fcould've taken steps to ensure the
OL,10,Ffire brigade were informed.
OL,12,F"He walked away, leaving the fire to
OL,13,Fspread and engulf the front of the
OL,14,Fhouse with the inevitable consequence
OL,15,Fthat the people inside would be
OL,16,Fseriously injured.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
